    "title": {
      "rendered": "HOW TO: Calculate Your Nonprofit&#8217;s Organic Reach on Facebook"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<div class=\"_4ng0\"><strong><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-20069\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"facebook-organic-reach-for-nonprofits\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Facebook-Organic-Reach-for-Nonprofits.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/help/285625061456389\" target=\"_blank\">According to Facebook</a></strong>, organic reach\u00a0is the total number of unique people who are shown your post(s) in their News Feed through unpaid distribution and although Facebook Insights provide a lot of useful data about your fans and reach (organic and paid), the one critical piece of data not provided is your nonprofit&#8217;s weekly, monthly, or quarterly <em>average</em> organic reach. Using the method below you can calculate your average monthly organic reach. You can also tweak the equation to calculate\u00a0your weekly, quarterly, or annual average organic reach.</div>\n<hr />\n<h1>1. Go to your nonprofit&#8217;s Facebook Page, select Insights &gt; Posts, and ensure that &#8220;Reach: Organic/Paid&#8221; is selected.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20059\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Insights-1.png?resize=600%2C296\" alt=\"insights-1\" width=\"600\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Insights-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Insights-1.png?resize=300%2C148&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1>2. Add up the organic reach for each post shared during a month.</h1>\n<p>To calculate your nonprofit&#8217;s monthly organic reach, add up the organic reach for each post shared during the month. If your nonprofit does not pay for advertising on Facebook, your nonprofit can keep it simple and use the rounded-to-the-nearest-hundred numbers. For example, we\u00a0added 3,600 + 2,700 + 7,500 + 1,200 + 9,600 + 847 + 1,200 + 909 and so forth for posts shared between September 9\u00a0and October 8 on the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Nonprofit Tech for Good Facebook Page</strong></a>:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20060\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Insights-2.png?resize=600%2C466\" alt=\"insights-2\" width=\"600\" height=\"466\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Insights-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Insights-2.png?resize=300%2C233&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If your nonprofit does pay for advertising, hover over the bar to see actual organic reach numbers:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20081\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/organic-and-paid.png?resize=600%2C94\" alt=\"organic-and-paid\" width=\"600\" height=\"94\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/organic-and-paid.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/organic-and-paid.png?resize=300%2C47&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1>3. Divide the sum of organic reach for posts\u00a0by the number of posts shared over the month.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Sum of Organic Reach for Posts (79,791)<br />\n<strong>\u00f7</strong><br />\n# of Posts Shared Over 1 Month (20)<br />\n<strong>=</strong><br />\n<strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">3,990: Average Monthly Reach for Posts</span></strong></h3>\n<h1>4) Convert your organic reach into a percentage.</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3,990 </span>\u00f7\u00a0# of Facebook Fans Your Page Has (100,178)<br />\n=<br />\n.0398 or .04 or 4%<br />\n<strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">4% Average Monthly Organic Reach for the Page</span></strong></h3>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">5) Conclude the results.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Over\u00a0the previous month, the <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\" target=\"_blank\">Nonprofit Tech for Good\u00a0Facebook Page</a></strong>\u00a0reached 4% of its fans through posts shared on the page. Put another way, 96% of the page&#8217;s 100,178 fans were not shown\u00a0the posts shared on the page. As mentioned in a <strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/09/21/the-insights-of-100000-nonprofit-technology-facebook-fans/\">previous post</a></strong>, that&#8217;s like sending an email to 100 people and having 96 of those emails blocked by email servers. That said, how many of the 4% of people actually saw and read the posts is unknown. Just because 4% of fans were shown\u00a0the posts in their News Feed over the last month, that doesn&#8217;t mean they actually saw and read them. <em><strong>That&#8217;s why organic reach is considered by many to be a\u00a0nonsensical number</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A more useful\u00a0metric to track is your &#8220;Engagement Rate.&#8221; Engagement is defined as people who liked/reacted, commented, clicked, or shared your posts. Following the same method above, go to\u00a0Insights &gt; Posts, and ensure that &#8220;Engagement Rate&#8221; is selected, and then do the math:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nonprofitorgs\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20063\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Percentages.png?resize=600%2C330\" alt=\"percentages\" width=\"600\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Percentages.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Percentages.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Sum of Engagement\u00a0Percentages (37.99)<br />\n\u00f7<br />\n# of Posts Shared Over 1 Month (20)<br />\n=<br />\n<strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">1.9%: Average Monthly Engagement for Posts on the Page\u00a0</span></strong>?</h3>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-20071 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/for-blog.jpg?resize=600%2C316\" alt=\"Web\" width=\"600\" height=\"316\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/for-blog.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/for-blog.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></h2>\n<h2>The survey for the 2017 Global NGO Online Technology Report is now available in <a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/5SNWNBT\" target=\"_blank\">English</a>, <a href=\"https://fr.surveymonkey.com/r/5SBVT8M\" target=\"_blank\">French</a>, and <a href=\"https://es.surveymonkey.com/r/5SWFNMQ\" target=\"_blank\">Spanish</a>. Your participation and promotion of the survey is greatly appreciated. With your help, we can reach this year\u2019s goal of 10,000 respondents.</h2>\n",
